  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9505032v2</id>
    <updated>1995-05-09T16:46:24Z</updated>
    <published>1995-05-08T18:16:53Z</published>
    <title>Superconductivity Fluctuations in a One-dimensional Two Band
  Electron-Phonon Model with Strong Repulsive Interactions</title>
    <summary>  We study a one-dimensional, two band model with short range electron-electron
repulsions (onsite $U$ and nearest-neighbour $V$ terms) and electron-phonon
coupling. We show that there is a region of $U$,$V$ and band filling in which
singlet superconductivity fluctuations are dominant. This region is absent
without electron-phonon interactions and includes large values of $U$,$V$.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>S. I. Matveenko</name>
    </author>
