    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9705012v1</id>
    <updated>1997-05-01T20:14:53Z</updated>
    <published>1997-05-01T20:14:53Z</published>
    <title>Quantum dots and artificial atoms</title>
    <summary>  The electronic properties of nanoscale quantum dots are reviewed. The
similarities and differences between these `artificial atoms' and real atoms
are discussed and, in particular, the effect of electron correlations is
examined. It is shown that for (semiconductor) quantum dots, with only a few
electrons, electron correlations can give rise to important new physics which
is absent in their true atomic counterparts.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>John H. Jefferson</name>
