  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9810159v1</id>
    <updated>1998-10-14T12:19:42Z</updated>
    <published>1998-10-14T12:19:42Z</published>
    <title>Stability of the maximum density droplet in quantum dots at high
  magnetic fields</title>
    <summary>  We have measured electron transport through a vertical quantum dot containing
a tunable number of electrons between 0 and 40. Over some region in magnetic
field the electrons are spin polarized and occupy successive angular momentum
states, i.e. the maximum density droplet (MDD) state. The stability region
where the MDD state is the ground state, decreases for increasing electron
number. The instability of the MDD is accompanied by a redistribution of charge
which increases the area of the electron droplet.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>T. H. Oosterkamp</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>J. W. Janssen</name>
    </author>
