  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9810355v2</id>
    <updated>1998-10-27T09:42:14Z</updated>
    <published>1998-10-26T23:44:41Z</published>
    <title>Superconductivity in correlated disordered two-dimensional electron gas</title>
    <summary>  We calculate the dynamic effective electron-electron interaction potential
for a low density disordered two-dimensional electron gas. The disordered
response function is used to calculate the effective potential where the
scattering rate is taken from typical mobilities from recent experiments. We
investigate the development of an effective attractive pair potential for both
disordered and disorder free systems with correlations determined from existing
numerical simulation data. The effect of disorder and correlations on the
superconducting critical temperature Tc is discussed.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>J. S. Thakur</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">University of New South Wales, Sydney, Australia</arxiv:affiliation>
