    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9905004v1</id>
    <updated>1999-05-01T12:26:48Z</updated>
    <published>1999-05-01T12:26:48Z</published>
    <title>Phase transitions of electron-hole and unbalanced electron systems in
  coupled quantum wells in high magnetic field</title>
    <summary>  Superfluidity of spatially separated electrons and holes and unbalanced
two-layer electron system in high magnetic field is considered.
 The temperature of the Kosterlitz-Thouless transition to a superfluid state is
obtained as a function of magnetic field and interlayer separation. The
equation of state for magnetoexciton system in quasi-classical regime is
analyzed. The transition from excitonic phase to electron-hole phase is
considered.
 Possible experimental manifestations of the predicted effects are briefly
discussed.
</summary>
