  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0004234v1</id>
    <updated>2000-04-14T06:59:06Z</updated>
    <published>2000-04-14T06:59:06Z</published>
    <title>Magnetoresistance of a two-dimensional electron gas in a parallel
  magnetic field</title>
    <summary>  The conductivity of a two-dimensional electron gas in a parallel magnetic
field is calculated. We take into account the magnetic field induced
spin-splitting, which changes the density of states, the Fermi momentum and the
screening behavior of the electron gas. For impurity scattering we predict a
positive magnetoresistance for low electron density and a negative
magnetoresistance for high electron density. The theory is in qualitative
agreement with recent experimental results found for Si inversion layers and Si
quantum wells.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>V. T. Dolgopolov</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Institute of Solid State Physics, Chernogolovka, Russia</arxiv:affiliation>
