  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0102001v1</id>
    <updated>2001-02-01T02:37:14Z</updated>
    <published>2001-02-01T02:37:14Z</published>
    <title>Chaos and Interactions in Quantum Dots</title>
    <summary>  Quantum dots are small conducting devices containing up to several thousand
electrons. We focus here on closed dots whose single-electron dynamics are
mostly chaotic. The mesoscopic fluctuations of the conduction properties of
such dots reveal the effects of one-body chaos, quantum coherence and
electron-electron interactions.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Y. Alhassid</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1238/Physica.Topical.090a00080</arxiv:doi>
