  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0111398v2</id>
    <updated>2003-07-17T06:58:23Z</updated>
    <published>2001-11-21T20:03:03Z</published>
    <title>Absence of electron dephasing at zero temperature</title>
    <summary>  Dephasing of electrons due to the electron-electron interaction has recently
been the subject of a controversial debate, with different calculations
yielding mutually incompatible results. In this paper we prove, by means of
Ward identities, that neither a Coulomb interaction nor a short-ranged model
interaction can lead to phase breaking at zero temperature in spatial
dimensions d&gt;2.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>T. R. Kirkpatrick</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>D. Belitz</name>
    </author>
