  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0203362v1</id>
    <updated>2002-03-18T21:39:47Z</updated>
    <published>2002-03-18T21:39:47Z</published>
    <title>Relaxation of Shallow Donor Electron Spin due to Interaction with
  Nuclear Spin Bath</title>
    <summary>  We study the low-temperature dynamics of a shallow donor, e.g., $^{31}$P,
impurity electron spin in silicon, interacting with the bath of nuclear spins
of the $^{29}$Si isotope. For small applied magnetic fields, the electron spin
relaxation is controlled by the steady state distribution of the nuclear spins.
We calculate the relaxation times $T_1$ and $T_2$ as functions of the external
magnetic field, and conclude that nuclear spins play an important role in the
donor electron spin decoherence in Si:P at low magnetic fields.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Semion Saykin</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Dima Mozyrsky</name>
