    <title>Quantum-dot lithium in strong-interaction regime: Depolarization of
  electron spins by magnetic field</title>
    <summary>  Magnetic field usually leads to a polarization of electron spins. It is shown
that in a system of {\em strongly interacting} particles applying magnetic
field may lead to an opposite effect -- depolarization of electron spins.
Results of the work are based on an exact-diagonalization study of quantum-dot
lithium -- a system of three Coulomb interacting two-dimensional electrons in a
parabolic confinement potential.
</summary>
