  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0304592v2</id>
    <updated>2003-10-21T02:07:16Z</updated>
    <published>2003-04-25T15:47:35Z</published>
    <title>Tunneling Density of States of the Interacting Two-Dimensional Electron
  Gas</title>
    <summary>  We investigate the influence of electron--electron interactions on the
density of states of a ballistic two--dimensional electron gas. The density of
states is determined nonperturbatively by means of path integral techniques
allowing for reliable results near the Fermi surface, where perturbation theory
breaks down. We find that the density of states is suppressed at the Fermi
level to a finite value. This suppression factor grows with decreasing electron
density and is weakened by the presence of gates.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Joerg Rollbuehler</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Hermann Grabert</name>
    </author>
