    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0306583v1</id>
    <updated>2003-06-23T20:27:58Z</updated>
    <published>2003-06-23T20:27:58Z</published>
    <title>Fluctuations of g-factors in metal nanoparticles: Effects of
  electron-electron interaction and spin-orbit scattering</title>
    <summary>  We investigate the combined effect of spin-orbit scattering and
electron-electron interactions on the probability distribution of $g$-factors
of metal nanoparticles. Using random matrix theory, we find that even a
relatively small interaction strength %(ratio of exchange constant $J$ and mean
level %spacing $\spacing$ $\simeq 0.3$) significantly increases $g$-factor
fluctuations for not-too-strong spin-orbit scattering (ratio of spin-orbit rate
and single-electron level spacing $1/\tau_{\rm so} \spacing \lesssim 1$), and
leads to the possibility to observe $g$-factors larger than two.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Denis A. Gorokhov</name>
    </author>
