    <title>Density of states of the interacting two-dimensional electron gas</title>
    <summary>  We study the influence of electron-electron interactions on the density of
states (DOS) of clean 2D electron gas. We confirm the linear cusp in the DOS
around the Fermi level, which was obtained previously. The cusp crosses over to
a pure logarithmic dependence further away from the Fermi surface.
</summary>
