  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0501516v1</id>
    <updated>2005-01-21T09:00:32Z</updated>
    <published>2005-01-21T09:00:32Z</published>
    <title>Electron cyclotron mass in undoped CdTe/CdMnTe quantum wells</title>
    <summary>  Optically detected cyclotron resonance of two-dimensional electrons has been
studied in nominally undoped CdTe/(Cd,Mn)Te quantum wells. The enhancement of
carrier quantum confinement results in an increase of the electron cyclotron
mass from 0.099$m_0 $ to 0.112$m_0 $ with well width decreasing from 30 down to
3.6 nm. Model calculations of the electron effective mass have been performed
for this material system and good agreement with experimental data is achieved
for an electron-phonon coupling constant $\alpha $=0.32.
</summary>
