  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0509547v1</id>
    <updated>2005-09-21T14:26:26Z</updated>
    <published>2005-09-21T14:26:26Z</published>
    <title>Nearly free electrons in the layered oxide superconductor Ag5Pb2O6</title>
    <summary>  We present first measurements of quantum oscillations in the layered oxide
superconductor
 Ag5Pb2O6. From a detailed angular and temperature dependent study of the dHvA
effect we determine the electronic structure and demonstrate that the electron
masses are very light, m^* is approximately equalt to 1.2 m_e. The Fermi
surface we observe is essentially that expected of nearly-free electrons -
establishing
 Ag5Pb2O6 as the first known example of a monovalent, nearly-free electron
superconductor at ambient pressure.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Mike Sutherland</name>
    </author>
