  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0602410v1</id>
    <updated>2006-02-17T11:28:20Z</updated>
    <published>2006-02-17T11:28:20Z</published>
    <title>Spin orientation of a two-dimensional electron gas by a high-frequency
  electric field</title>
    <summary>  Coupling of spin states and space motion of conduction electrons due to
spin-orbit interaction opens up possibilities for manipulation of the electron
spins by electrical means. It is shown here that spin orientation of a
two-dimensional electron gas can be achieved by excitation of the carriers with
a linearly polarized high-frequency electric field. In (001)-grown quantum well
structures excitation with in-plane ac electric field induces orientation of
the electron spins along the quantum well normal, with the spin sign and the
magnitude depending on the field polarization.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>S. A. Tarasenko</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevB.73.115317</arxiv:doi>
