  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0603339v1</id>
    <updated>2006-03-13T09:43:47Z</updated>
    <published>2006-03-13T09:43:47Z</published>
    <title>Role of electron-electron and electron-phonon interaction effect in the
  optical conductivity of VO2</title>
    <summary>  We have investigated the charge dynamics of VO2 by optical reflectivity
measurements. Optical conductivity clearly shows a metal-insulator transition.
In the metallic phase, a broad Drude-like structure is observed. On the other
hand, in the insulating phase, a broad peak structure around 1.3 eV is
observed. It is found that this broad structure observed in the insulating
phase shows a temperature dependence. We attribute this to the electron-phonon
interaction as in the photoemission spectra.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>K. Okazaki</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>S. Sugai</name>
