    <title>Comment on Phys. Rev. Lett.'s paper "All-Electron Self-Consistent GW
  Approximation: Application to Si, MnO, and NiO": band vs localized
  description of NiO</title>
    <summary>  In contrary to authors of Phys. Rev. Lett. 93, 126406 (2004) claiming "the
band picture to be a reasonable starting point for the description of the
electronic structure of NiO, much better than the ligand-field picture", we
argue that the many-electron CEF approach is physically adequate starting point
