    <title>Study of the Fundamental Structure of Matter with an Electron-Ion
  Collider</title>
    <summary>  We present an overview of the scientific opportunities that would be offered
by a high-energy electron-ion collider. We discuss the relevant physics of
polarized and unpolarized electron-proton collisions and of electron-nucleus
collisions. We also describe the current accelerator and detector plans for a
future electron-ion collider.
</summary>
