  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/physics/9902013v1</id>
    <updated>1999-02-05T10:48:10Z</updated>
    <published>1999-02-05T10:48:10Z</published>
    <title>A Compton Backscattering Polarimeter for Measuring Longitudinal Electron
  Polarization</title>
    <summary>  Compton backscattering polarimetry provides a fast measurement of the
polarization of an electron beam in a storage ring. Since the method is
non-destructive, the polarization of the electrons can be monitored during
internal target experiments. At NIKHEF a Compton polarimeter has been
constructed to measure the polarization of the longitudinally polarized
electrons stored in the AmPS ring. First results obtained with the polarimeter,
the first Compton polarimeter to measure the polarization of a stored
longitudinally polarized electron beam, are presented in this paper.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>I. Passchier</name>
    </author>
    <author>
