  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0208018v1</id>
    <updated>2002-08-05T09:33:59Z</updated>
    <published>2002-08-05T09:33:59Z</published>
    <title>Bunch coherence in parametric X-ray radiation</title>
    <summary>  The amplitude of Parametric X-ray radiation emitted coherently by a bunch of
electrons crossing a crystal (CPXR) is calculated. When the bunch density is
modulated with a longitudinal period close to the X-ray wavelenght,
constructive many-electron interferences enhance the intensity by Nb *
|F(K)|^2, where Nb is the number of electrons in the bunch, F(K) the bunch form
factor and K a specified wave vector. CPXR can be used to test the
microbunching in a X-ray free-electron laser.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Xavier Artru</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Karo A. Ispirian</name>
    </author>
