  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0306061v1</id>
    <updated>2003-06-07T15:24:26Z</updated>
    <published>2003-06-07T15:24:26Z</published>
    <title>Precision calculations of atoms with few valence electrons</title>
    <summary>  We discuss the possibility of using pair-equations for the construction of
the effective Hamiltonian $H_{\rm eff}$ for valence electrons of an atom. The
low-energy part of atomic spectrum is found by solving the eigenvalue problem
for $H_{\rm eff}$. In this way it is possible to account efficiently for the
valence-valence and core-valence correlations. We tested this method on a toy
model of a four-electron atom with the core $1s^2$. The spectrum obtained with
$H_{\rm eff}$ for two valence electrons is in a perfect agreement with the full
configuration interaction for all four electrons.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M G Kozlov</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Talk at the VI Fock school, Novgorod, Russia. 11 pages, 6 figures</arxiv:comment>
