  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0512047v2</id>
    <updated>2006-04-10T08:37:25Z</updated>
    <published>2005-12-06T17:39:47Z</published>
    <title>Some remarks about mass and Zitterbewegung substructure of electron</title>
    <summary>  It is shown that the electron Zitterbewegung, that is, the high-frequency
microscopic oscillatory motion of electron about its centre of mass, originates
a spatial distribution of charge. This allows the point-like electron behave
like a particle of definite size whose self-energy, that is, energy of its
electromagnetic field, owns a finite value. This has implications for the
electron mass, which, in principle, might be derived from Zitterbewegung
physics.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>P. Brovetto</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>V. Maxia</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>M. Salis</name>
    </author>
