  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0609059v1</id>
    <updated>2006-09-08T05:24:36Z</updated>
    <published>2006-09-08T05:24:36Z</published>
    <title>Shannon entropies of atomic structure factors, off-diagonal order and
  electron correlation</title>
    <summary>  Shannon entropies of one- and two-electron atomic structure factors in the
position and momentum representations are used to examine the behavior of the
off-diagonal elements of density matrices with respect to the uncertainty
principle and to analyze the effects of electron correlation on off-diagonal
order. We show that electron correlation induces off-diagonal order in position
space which is characterized by larger entropic values. Electron correlation in
momentum space is characterized by smaller entropic values as information is
forced into regions closer to the diagonal. Related off-diagonal correlation
functions are also discussed.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Robin P. Sagar</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Nicolais L. Guevara</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1080/00268970701335771</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00268970701335771" rel="related"/>
    <arxiv:journal_ref xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Mol. Phys. 105 (2007) 1359-1368</arxiv:journal_ref>
    <link href="http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0609059v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link title="pdf" href="http://arxiv.org/pdf/quant-ph/0609059v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf"/>
