  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/0807.2531v3</id>
    <updated>2009-07-20T12:30:08Z</updated>
    <published>2008-07-16T09:50:49Z</published>
    <title>Absence of diffusion in certain random lattices: Numerical evidence</title>
    <summary>  We demonstrate, by solving numerically the time-dependent Schroedinger
equation, the physical character of electron localization in a disordered
two-dimensional lattice. We show, in agreement with the prediction of P. W.
Anderson, that the disorder prevents electron diffusion. The electron becomes
spatially localized in a specific area of the system. Our numerical analysis
confirms that the electron localization is a quantum effect caused by the wave
character of electron propagation and has no analogy in classical mechanics.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Peter Markos</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">*.png figures</arxiv:comment>
