    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1402.1963v1</id>
    <updated>2014-02-09T16:43:05Z</updated>
    <published>2014-02-09T16:43:05Z</published>
    <title>Using k-alpha emission to determine fast electron spectra using the
  Hybrid code ZEPHYROS</title>
    <summary>  A high intensity laser-solid interaction invariably drives a non-thermal fast
electron current through the target, however characterizing these fast electron
distributions can prove difficult. An understanding of how these electrons
propagate through dense materials is of fundamental interest and has
applications relevant to fast ignition schemes and ion acceleration. Here, we
utilize an upgraded version of the Hybrid code ZEPHYROS to demonstrate how the
resulting k-alpha emission from such an interaction can be used as a diagnostic
to obtain the characteristic temperature, divergence and total energy of the
fast electron population.
</summary>
