  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1403.2615v1</id>
    <updated>2014-03-11T15:33:30Z</updated>
    <published>2014-03-11T15:33:30Z</published>
    <title>Nonlinear electromagnetic response of a uniform electron gas</title>
    <summary>  The linear electromagnetic response of a uniform electron gas to a
longitudinal electric field is determined, within the self-consistent-field
theory, by the linear polarizability and the Lindhard dielectric function.
Using the same approach we derive analytical expressions for the second- and
third-order nonlinear polarizabilities of the three-, two- and one-dimensional
homogeneous electron gases with the parabolic electron energy dispersion. The
results are valid both for degenerate (Fermi) and non-degenerate (Boltzmann)
electron gases. A resonant enhancement of the second and third harmonics
generation due to a combination of the single-particle and collective (plasma)
resonances is predicted.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>S. A. Mikhailov</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.113.027405</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.113.027405" rel="related"/>
