    <published>2014-12-03T15:15:19Z</published>
    <title>Monte-Carlo study of the phase transition in the AA-stacked bilayer
  graphene</title>
    <summary>  Tight-binding model of the AA-stacked bilayer graphene with screened
electron-electron interactions has been studied using the Hybrid Monte Carlo
simulations on the original double-layer hexagonal lattice. Instantaneous
screened Coulomb potential is taken into account using Hubbard-Stratonovich
transformation. G-type antiferromagnetic ordering has been studied and the
phase transition with spontaneous generation of the mass gap has been observed.
Dependence of the antiferromagnetic condensate on the on-site electron-electron
interaction is examined.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>A. A. Nikolaev</name>
    </author>
