    <published>2015-06-24T00:57:27Z</published>
    <title>A quantum mechanical scheme to reduce radiation damage in electron
  microscopy</title>
    <summary>  We show that radiation damage to unstained biological specimens is not an
intractable problem in electron microscopy. When a structural hypothesis of a
specimen is available, quantum mechanical principles allow us to verify the
hypothesis with a very low electron dose. Realization of such a concept
requires precise control of the electron wave front. Based on a diffractive
electron optical implementation, we demonstrate the feasibility of this new
method by both experimental and numerical investigations.
</summary>
