  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1509.06635v4</id>
    <updated>2015-11-25T02:34:52Z</updated>
    <published>2015-09-22T18:50:16Z</published>
    <title>Bremsstrahlung from few-electron ions</title>
    <summary>  A new approach is developed to determine bremsstrahlung from few-electron
ions and atoms. Our approach is based on the explicit formula for the electron
density distribution in such systems. We derive the closed analytical formula
for the matrix elements which are needed for highly accurate computations of
atomic form-factors of two-electron atoms and ions. We also discuss the energy
loss due to bremsstrahlung in a plasma which contains multi-charged ions and
free electrons. Bremsstrahlung from high-temperature plasma is considered as
well as its role in the high-temperature burn-up of deuterium plasma.
</summary>
    <author>
