  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/astro-ph/9502003v1</id>
    <updated>1995-02-01T21:32:06Z</updated>
    <published>1995-02-01T21:32:06Z</published>
    <title>Solar Neutrinos: Radiative Corrections in Neutrino-Electron Scattering
  Experiments</title>
    <summary>Radiative corrections to the electron recoil-energy spectra and to total cross
sections are computed for neutrino-electron scattering by solar neutrinos.
Radiative corrections change monotonically the electron recoil spectrum for
incident \b8 neutrinos, with the relative probability of observing recoil
electrons being reduced by about 4 \% at the highest electron energies. For
$p-p$ and $\be7$ neutrinos, the recoil spectra are not affected significantly.
Total cross sections for solar neutrino-electron scattering are reduced by
about 2 \% compared to previously computed values. We also calculate the recoil
spectra from $^{13}$N and $^{15}$O neutrinos including radiative corrections.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>John N. Bahcall</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Marc Kamionkowski</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Alberto Sirlin</name>
    </author>
