  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0701240v1</id>
    <updated>2007-01-11T12:07:47Z</updated>
    <published>2007-01-11T12:07:47Z</published>
    <title>Charge Ordering in Amorphous WO$_{x}$ Films</title>
    <summary>  We report on the observation of highly anisotropic viscous electronic
conducting phase in amorphous WO$_{1.55}$ films that occurs below a current
(I)- and frequency (f)- dependent temperature T*(I, f). At T &lt; T*(I, f) the
rotational symmetry of randomly disordered electronic background is broken
leading to the appearance of mutually perpendicular metallic- and
insulating-like states. A rich dynamic behavior of the electronic matter
occurring at T &lt; T*(I, f) provides evidence for an interplay between pinning
effects and electron-electron interactions. The results strongly suggest a
dynamic crystallization of the disordered electronic matter, viz. formation of
sliding Wigner crystal, as well as the occurrence of quantum smectic or stripe
phase in the pinning-dominated regime.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Yakov Kopelevich</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Robson R. da Silva</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Aline Rougier</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Igor A. Lukyanchuk</name>
    </author>
