  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1102.3275v2</id>
    <updated>2011-04-23T06:25:32Z</updated>
    <published>2011-02-16T09:35:43Z</published>
    <title>Electron Mass Enhancement due to Anharmonic Local Phonons</title>
    <summary>  In order to understand how electron effective mass is enhanced by anharmonic
local oscillation of an atom in a cage composed of other atoms, i.e., {\it
rattling}, we analyze anharmonic Holstein model by using a Green's function
method. Due to the evaluation of an electron mass enhancement factor $Z$, we
find that $Z$ becomes maximum when zero-point energy is comparable with
potential height at which the amplitude of oscillation is rapidly enlarged.
Cooperation of such quantum and rattling effects is considered to be a key
issue to explain the electron mass enhancement in electron-rattling systems.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Kunihiro Oshiba</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Takashi Hotta</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1143/JPSJS.80SA.SA134</arxiv:doi>
