  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1306.2720v2</id>
    <updated>2013-06-19T14:19:03Z</updated>
    <published>2013-06-12T05:58:31Z</published>
    <title>Coherence and Screening in Multi-Electron Spin Qubits</title>
    <summary>  The performance of multi-electron spin qubits is examined by comparing
exchange oscillations in coupled single-electron and multi-electron quantum
dots in the same device. Fast (&gt; 1 GHz) exchange oscillations with a quality
factor Q &gt; 15 are found for the multi-electron case, compared to Q ~ 2 for the
single-electron case, the latter consistent with previous experiments. A model
of dephasing that includes voltage and hyperfine noise is developed that is in
good agreement with both single- and multi-electron data, though in both cases
additional exchange-independent dephasing is needed to obtain quantitative
agreement across a broad parameter range.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>A. P. Higginbotham</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>F. Kuemmeth</name>
    </author>
