    <title>Engineering Superfluidity in Electron-Hole Double Layers</title>
    <summary>  We show that band-structure effects are likely to prevent superfluidity in
semiconductor electron-hole double-layer systems. We suggest the possibility
that superfluidity could be realized by the application of uniaxial pressure
perpendicular to the electron and hole layers.
</summary>
