    <title>Effective mass at the surface of a Fermi liquid</title>
    <summary>  Using the dynamical mean-field theory, we calculate the effective electron
mass in the Hubbard model on a semi-infinite lattice. At the surface the
effective mass is strongly enhanced. Near half-filling this gives rise to a
correlation-driven one-electron surface mode.
</summary>
