    <title>3D Anderson transition for two electrons in 2D</title>
    <summary>  It is shown that the Coulomb interaction can lead to delocalization of two
electron states in two-dimensional (2D) disordered potential in a way similar
to the Anderson transition in three dimensions (3D). At fixed disorder strength
the localized phase corresponds to low electron density and large value of
parameter r_s.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>D. L. Shepelyansky</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">CNRS, Toulouse, France</arxiv:affiliation>
