  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9904174v1</id>
    <updated>1999-04-13T11:15:02Z</updated>
    <published>1999-04-13T11:15:02Z</published>
    <title>Non-Fermi behavior of the disorder electronic system</title>
    <summary>  We showed that an electronic system with weak disorder considered in the
finite-charge infinite U Hubbard model can present a non-Fermi behavior. The
imaginary pert of the self-energy has been calculated and a linear temperature
dependence was obtained. This result is in agreement with the non-Fermi
behavior observed at the insulator-metal crossover in La_{2-x}Sr_xCuO_4.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>C. P. Moca</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>I. Tifrea</name>
    </author>
