    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9904308v1</id>
    <updated>1999-04-21T20:08:19Z</updated>
    <published>1999-04-21T20:08:19Z</published>
    <title>On the thermodynamics of strongly correlated integrable electron systems</title>
    <summary>  We reexamine the Yang-Yang-Takahashi method of deriving the thermodynamic
Bethe ansatz equations which describe strongly correlated electron systems of
fundamental physical interest, such as the Hubbard, $s-d$ exchange (Kondo) and
Anderson models. It is shown that these equations contain some additional terms
which may play an important role in the physics of the systems.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Valery I. Rupasov</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">U. of Toronto and Landau Institute</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
