  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9912270v1</id>
    <updated>1999-12-15T00:39:21Z</updated>
    <published>1999-12-15T00:39:21Z</published>
    <title>Confinement of Slave-Particles in U(1) Gauge Theories of
  Strongly-Interacting Electrons</title>
    <summary>  We show that slave particles are always confined in U(1) gauge theories of
interacting electron systems. Consequently, the low-lying degrees of freedom
are different from the slave particles. This is done by constructing a dual
formulation of the slave-particle representation in which the no-double
occupany constraint becomes linear and, hence, soluble. Spin-charge separation,
if it occurs, is due to the existence of solitons with fractional quantum
numbers.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Chetan Nayak</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">UCLA</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.85.178</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.85.178" rel="related"/>
    <link href="http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9912270v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
