    <title>On the formation of Wigner molecules in small quantum dots</title>
    <summary>  It was recently argued that in small quantum dots the electrons could
crystallize at much higher densities than in the infinite two-dimensional
electron gas. We compare predictions that the onset of spin polarization and
the formation of Wigner molecules occurs at a density parameter $r_s\approx 4
a_B^*$ to the results of a straight-forward diagonalization of the Hamiltonian
matrix.
</summary>
