  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0102236v1</id>
    <updated>2001-02-13T15:22:03Z</updated>
    <published>2001-02-13T15:22:03Z</published>
    <title>Resonant electron transmission through a finite quantum spin chain</title>
    <summary>  Electron transport in a finite one dimensional quantum spin chain (with
ferromagnetic exchange) is studied within an $s-d$ exchange Hamiltonian. Spin
transfer coefficients strongly depend on the sign of the $s-d$ exchange
constant. For a ferromagnetic coupling, they exhibit a novel resonant pattern,
reflecting the salient features of the combined electron-spin system. Spin-flip
processes are inelastic and feasible at finite voltage or at finite
temperature.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Y. Avishai</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Y. Tokura</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.87.197203</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.87.197203" rel="related"/>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">4 pages including 4 .eps figures</arxiv:comment>
