  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0106526v1</id>
    <updated>2001-06-26T20:35:17Z</updated>
    <published>2001-06-26T20:35:17Z</published>
    <title>Nonlinear conductivity of diffusive normal-metal contacts</title>
    <summary>  Metal microbridges with a high impurity content and shorter than the energy
relaxation length are considered. Their conductance is calculated with
allowance made for the Coulomb electron-electron interaction. It is shown that
nonequilibrium electrons in the microbridges gives rise to a nonlinear
current-voltage characteristic (published in Physics Letters A, 1994).
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>K. E. Nagaev</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1016/0375-9601(94)90832-X</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0375-9601(94)90832-X" rel="related"/>
