    <published>2001-11-21T14:42:09Z</published>
    <title>Comment on ``Quantum Pump for Spin and Charge Transport in a Luttinger
  Liquid''</title>
    <summary>  This is a Comment to the paper by Sharma and Chamon in Phys. Rev. Lett. 87
(2001) 096401 (cond-mat/0011025). We show that the prediction of the universal
charge pumped per cycle in the fast limit for attractive electron-electron
interaction is invalid. We also prove the quantization of the pumped charge for
repulsive interaction in the limit of adiabatic pumping.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Dima E. Feldman</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Yuval Gefen</name>
    </author>
