    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0403765v1</id>
    <updated>2004-03-31T16:00:47Z</updated>
    <published>2004-03-31T16:00:47Z</published>
    <title>Mott--Hubbard transition vs. Anderson localization of correlated,
  disordered electrons</title>
    <summary>  The phase diagram of correlated, disordered electrons is calculated within
dynamical mean--field theory using the geometrically averaged (''typical'')
local density of states. Correlated metal, Mott insulator and Anderson
insulator phases, as well as coexistence and crossover regimes are identified.
The Mott and Anderson insulators are found to be continuously connected.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Krzysztof Byczuk</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Walter Hofstetter</name>
    </author>
