    <updated>2004-12-22T16:25:34Z</updated>
    <published>2004-12-22T16:25:34Z</published>
    <title>Bound states in the phase diagram of the extended Hubbard model</title>
    <summary>  The papaer shows how the known, exact results for the two electron bound
states can modify the ground state phase diagram of extended Hubbard model
(EHM) for on-site attraction, intersite repulsion and arbitrary electron
density. The main result is suppression of the superconducting state in favor
of normal phase for small charge densities.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M. Bak</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1002/pssb.200460049</arxiv:doi>
