  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0603313v1</id>
    <updated>2006-03-11T13:17:59Z</updated>
    <published>2006-03-11T13:17:59Z</published>
    <title>Electronic Structure and Magnetic Properties of $β$-Ti$_{6}$Sn$_{5}$</title>
    <summary>  The electronic structure of $\beta$-Ti$_{6}$Sn$_{5}$ has been studied based
on the density functional theory within the local-density approximation. The
calculation indicates that $\beta$-Ti$_{6}$Sn$_{5}$ is very close to
ferromagnetic instability and shows ferromagnetic ordering after rare earth
element doping. Large enhancement of the static susceptibility over its
non-interacting value is found due to a peak in the density of states at the
Fermi level.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>T. Jeong</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1016/j.jmmm.2006.05.030</arxiv:doi>
