    <title>Influence of the finite deformations changing the symmetry of an initial
  lattice on a generation of atoms displacements waves by non-equilibrium
  electrons</title>
    <summary>  For the model electronic spectrum in the tight-binding approximation it is
shown that the finite homogeneous deformation essentially increases the
quantity of pairs of electronic states which are active in generation of atoms
displacement waves. This conclusion gives additional possibilities for the
explanation of features of the process of martensitic transformation.
</summary>
