    <title>Current instability and single-mode THz generation in ungated
  two-dimensional electron gas</title>
    <summary>  We analyze the current instability of the steady state with a direct current
for an ungated two-dimensional(2D) electron layer for arbitrary current and the
carrier scattering strength. We demonstrate the possibility of single-mode
generator operating in terahertz frequency range.
