    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0606414v1</id>
    <updated>2006-06-15T14:29:04Z</updated>
    <published>2006-06-15T14:29:04Z</published>
    <title>Multiple transitions of the spin configuration in quantum dots</title>
    <summary>  Single electron tunneling is studied in a many electron quantum dot in high
magnetic fields. For such a system multiple transitions of the spin
configuration are theoretically predicted. With a combination of spin blockade
and Kondo effect we are able to detect five regions with different spin
configurations. Transitions are induced with changing electron numbers.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M. C. Rogge</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>C. Fuhner</name>
    </author>
