    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/nucl-th/9411030v1</id>
    <updated>1994-11-24T16:32:36Z</updated>
    <published>1994-11-24T16:32:36Z</published>
    <title>The Effective Non-Relativistic Hamiltonian for Electron-Nucleus
  Interaction</title>
    <summary>  We present the effective Hamiltonian for an electron-nucleus interaction in
non-relativistic limit up to the second order in the inverse nucleon mass. This
Hamiltonian takes into account the distortion of electron waves and allows to
calculate its effect as well as matrix elements for off-shell transitions in
$(e,e'p)$ reactions.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>R. Ya. Kezerashvili</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Dipartimento di Fisica, Universita'di Pisa and INFN, Sezione di Pisa</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
