    <title>Classical Electron Theory and Conservation Laws</title>
    <summary>  It is shown that the traditional conservation laws for total charge, energy,
linear and angular momentum, hold jointly in classical electron theory if and
only if classical electron spin is included as dynamical degree of freedom.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Michael K. -H. Kiessling</name>
    </author>
