    <title>An easy method to estimate charge-exchange cross sections between ions
  and one-active-electron atoms</title>
    <summary>  In this paper we present a simple model for computing single electron
exchange between light nuclei. The electronic capture is pictured as a
tunnelling process in a model potential. This allows to analytically compute
the transmission probability. Some comparisons with data from existing
literature are given.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Fabio Sattin</name>
