    <title>Three-dimensional PIC simulation of electron plasmas</title>
    <summary>  The three-dimensional evolution of a pure electron plasma is studied by means
of a particle-in-cell code which solves the drift-Poisson system where kinetic
effects in the motion parallel to the magnetic field are taken into account.
Different results relevant to the nonlinear dynamics of trapped plasmas and
low-energy electron beams are presented.
</summary>
