    <title>Interface effects and termination of finite length nanotubes</title>
    <summary>  The objective of the present paper is to investigate interface effects in
carbon nanotubes. We use both real and k-space tight binding method. We study
in detail the effect of wrapping vector on the electronic properties. We
analyze the effect of the curvature in closed nanotube to the electronic
properties. The finite length of the nanotube affects the electronic
properties.
</summary>
