    <title>The structure and dynamics of solvated electron in polar liquids</title>
    <summary>  A review with 106 references of the recent advances in understanding the
structure, dynamics, and photodynamics of solvated electrons in polar liquids
(and, to some degree, clusters): water, alcohols, ammonia, ethers. Both the
orthodox (cavity) and heterodox (multimer anion) pictures of the solvated
electron are discussed.
</summary>
