    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0411150v1</id>
    <updated>2004-11-19T17:10:11Z</updated>
    <published>2004-11-19T17:10:11Z</published>
    <title>Cylindrical quantum well of finite depth in external magnetic field</title>
    <summary>  Energy spectrum of an electron confined by finite hard-wall potential in a
cylinder quantum dot placed in weak (up to 100 kOe) homogeneous external
magnetic field were calculated using the method of variation of vector
potential. Electronic motion along the cylinder axis is limited by
one-dimensional infinite potential barrier and electronic motion on the plane
perpendicular to the axis is limited by two-dimensional finite potential
barrier.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>O. R. Lobanova</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>A. I. Ivanov</name>
