    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0504142v2</id>
    <updated>2005-04-19T20:06:56Z</updated>
    <published>2005-04-19T19:48:45Z</published>
    <title>Bound states in continuum in an electron waveguide</title>
    <summary>  It is shown that in a double-cavity, two-dimensional electron waveguide, the
interplay between quasi-bound states of each cavity leads to the appearance of
bound states in continuum for certain distances between the cavities. These
bound states may be used to trap electrons in de-localized states distributed
in both cavities.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Kyungsun Na</name>
