  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0608084v1</id>
    <updated>2006-08-09T20:17:27Z</updated>
    <published>2006-08-09T20:17:27Z</published>
    <title>A three grating electron interferometer</title>
    <summary>  We report the observation of fringes from a three grating electron
interferometer. Interference fringes have been observed at low energies ranging
from 6 keV to 10 keV. Contrasts of up to 25% are recorded and exceed the
maximal contrast of the classical equivalent, Moire deflectometer. This type of
interferometer could serve as a separate beam Mach-Zehnder interferometer for
low energy electron interferometry experiments.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Glen Gronniger</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Brett Barwick</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Herman Batelaan</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1088/1367-2630/8/10/224</arxiv:doi>
