  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0610169v1</id>
    <updated>2006-10-20T08:20:23Z</updated>
    <published>2006-10-20T08:20:23Z</published>
    <title>Loschmidt echo in a system of interacting electrons</title>
    <summary>  We study the Loschmidt echo for a system of electrons interacting through
mean-field Coulomb forces. The electron gas is modeled by a self-consistent set
of hydrodynamic equations. It is observed that the quantum fidelity drops
abruptly after a time that is proportional to the logarithm of the perturbation
amplitude. The fidelity drop is related to the breakdown of the symmetry
properties of the wave function.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>G. Manfredi</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>P. -A. Hervieux</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.97.190404</arxiv:doi>
