  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/0707.3822v1</id>
    <updated>2007-07-25T20:50:31Z</updated>
    <published>2007-07-25T20:50:31Z</published>
    <title>Study of the spin-$\frac32$ Hubbard-Kondo lattice model by means of the
  Composite Operator Method</title>
    <summary>  We study the spin-$\frac32$ Hubbard-Kondo lattice model by means of the
Composite Operator Method, after applying a Holstein-Primakov transformation.
The spin and particle dynamics in the ferromagnetic state are calculated by
taking into account strong on-site correlations between electrons and
antiferromagnetic exchange among $\frac32$ spins, together with usual Hund
coupling between electrons and spins.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Adolfo Avella</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Ferdinando Mancini</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1016/j.physb.2006.01.227</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.physb.2006.01.227" rel="related"/>
