    <title>Modeling single- and multiple-electron resonances for
  electric-field-sensitive scanning probes</title>
    <summary>  We have developed a modeling method suitable to analyze single- and
multiple-electron resonances detected by electric-field-sensitive scanning
probe techniques. The method is based on basic electrostatics and a numerical
boundary-element approach. The results compare well to approximate analytical
expressions and experimental data.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>S. H. Tessmer</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>I. Kuljanishvili</name>
