  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/0907.4125v1</id>
    <updated>2009-07-23T17:25:17Z</updated>
    <published>2009-07-23T17:25:17Z</published>
    <title>The Electron-Ion Collider</title>
    <summary>  The future Electron-Ion Collider (EIC) is a proposed new facility to collide
high-energy electrons with beams of polarized protons/light nuclei and
unpolarized nuclei. We overview the goals of the project and key measurements
at the EIC. We also briefly comment on recent developments of the project.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>V. Guzey</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Jefferson Lab</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1063/1.3293930</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1063/1.3293930" rel="related"/>
