  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/0910.4030v1</id>
    <updated>2009-10-21T09:56:14Z</updated>
    <published>2009-10-21T09:56:14Z</published>
    <title>Investigation of electrons interaction in a superconductor</title>
    <summary>  Investigating the interaction of electrons in a superconductor by means of a
method of solitary waves of Korteweg - de Vries, we refute the claim of absence
of "Cooper pairs" in a superconductor. We also indicate that the nondissipative
transfer of energy in the superconductor is possible only with the help of a
pair of electrons.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Iogann Tolbatov</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">7 pages, 0 figures</arxiv:comment>
    <arxiv:journal_ref xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Journal Izvestiya VUZov. Pish. Tech.; Krasnodar, 2007; 8 p., bibl.
  19.; Rus.; Published in VINITI RAN 27.12.2007, N 1252 B2007</arxiv:journal_ref>
    <link href="http://arxiv.org/abs/0910.4030v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link title="pdf" href="http://arxiv.org/pdf/0910.4030v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf"/>
