  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1001.0643v1</id>
    <updated>2010-01-05T18:35:28Z</updated>
    <published>2010-01-05T18:35:28Z</published>
    <title>Response to I. I. Mazin's correspondence on "Electronic correlations in
  the iron pnictides"</title>
    <summary>  We discuss the discrepancy between the measured optical Drude weight and band
structure calculations in LaFePO and other iron-based superconductors. This
discrepancy is mostly due to mass renormalization arising from electronic
correlation effects.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M. M. Qazilbash</name>
