    <title>Polarization Dependence of Optical Transitions in Graphene Nanoribbons</title>
    <summary>  The universality of $k$-dependent electron-photon and electron-phonon matrix
elements is discussed for graphene nanoribbons and carbon nanotubes. An
electron undergoes a change in wavevector in the direction of broken
translational symmetry, depending on the light polarization direction. We
suggest that this phenomenon originates from a microscopic feature of
chirality.
</summary>
