  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1007.1416v1</id>
    <updated>2010-07-08T16:55:00Z</updated>
    <published>2010-07-08T16:55:00Z</published>
    <title>Two-center resonant photo ionization</title>
    <summary>  Photoionization of an atom $A$, in the presence of a neighboring atom $B$,
can proceed via resonant excitation of $B$ with subsequent energy transfer to
$A$ through two-center electron-electron correlation. We demonstrate that this
two-center mechanism can strongly outperform direct photoionization at
nanometer internuclear distances and possesses characteristic features in its
time development and the spectrum of emitted electrons.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>B. Najjari</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>A. B. Voitkiv</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>C. Müller</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.105.153002</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.105.153002" rel="related"/>
