    <title>Spin flip probability of electron in a uniform magnetic field</title>
    <summary>  The probability of a spin flip of an electron is calculated. It is assumed
that the electron resides in a uniform magnetic field and interacts with an
incoming electromagnetic pulse. The scattering matrix is constructed and the
time needed to flip the spin is calculated.
</summary>
