  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1306.2925v1</id>
    <updated>2013-06-12T19:04:56Z</updated>
    <published>2013-06-12T19:04:56Z</published>
    <title>Contribution of the Electron-Phonon Coupling to the Pairing Interaction
  in LiFeAs</title>
    <summary>  The coupling strengths for intra- and inter-band electron-phonon pair
scattering are calculated for LiFeAs. While the sum of these couplings, which
gives the total electron-phonon coupling $\lambda$, is of order 0.2, we find
that their contribution to the presumed $s^\pm$ superconducting state is
reduced by approximately an order of magnitude.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>R. A. Jishi</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Douglas Scalapino</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevB.88.184505</arxiv:doi>
