    <title>Effect of electron-phonon interactions on Raman line at ferromagnetic
  ordering</title>
    <summary>  The theory of Raman scattering in half-metals by optical phonons interacting
with conduction electrons is developed. We evaluate the effect of
electron-phonon interactions at ferromagnetic ordering in terms of the
Boltzmann equation for carriers. The chemical potential is found to decrease
with temperature decreasing. Both the linewidth and frequency shift exhibit a
dependence on temperature.
</summary>
