    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1412.5887v1</id>
    <updated>2014-12-18T15:19:53Z</updated>
    <published>2014-12-18T15:19:53Z</published>
    <title>Is the electron stationary in the ground state of the Dirac hydrogen
  atom in Bohm's Theory?</title>
    <summary>  We show that, in the relativistic Bohm model of a Dirac-like particle, the
electron in the ground state of the hydrogen atom is moving, unlike the
prediction for the case of a Schr\"{o}dinger-like particle, where the electron
is stationary. This accounts for the empirically observed dilation of the decay
time of the muon in the ground state of muonium.
</summary>
    <author>
