    <published>2015-11-04T21:38:39Z</published>
    <title>On highly accurate computations of some properties of the negatively
  charged positronium and hydrogen ions</title>
    <summary>  Numerical values of some important electron-positron and electron-electron
expectation values are reported for the ground (bound) $1^1S-$state of the
negatively charged Ps$^{-}$ and H$^{-}$ ions. Convergence of these values upon
the total number of basis functions $N$ used is briefly discussed.
</summary>
    <author>
