  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/1512.00261v1</id>
    <updated>2015-12-01T14:08:34Z</updated>
    <published>2015-12-01T14:08:34Z</published>
    <title>Hidden structure in the excitation spectra of strongly correlated
  electrons</title>
    <summary>  Distinct regimes of behaviour of strongly correlated electrons are
identified, characterised by a structure in their excitation spectra away from
the Fermi surface. This is clearly mapped out in an extended 1D Hubbard model,
which possesses a number of exactly solvable lines. It is further argued that
this physics is also present in higher dimensions.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Eoin Quinn</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">4+2 pages</arxiv:comment>
