  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/astro-ph/0601459v2</id>
    <updated>2006-01-23T09:51:55Z</updated>
    <published>2006-01-19T22:20:49Z</published>
    <title>Thermalisation of electrons in a stellar atmosphere</title>
    <summary>  We are interested in electrons kinetics in a stellar atmosphere to validate
or invalidate the usually accepted hypothesis of thermalisation of electrons.
For this purpose, we calculate the velocity distribution function of electrons
by solving the kinetic equation of these particles together with the equations
of radiative transfer and statistical equilibrium. We note that this
distribution can deviate strongly from a Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution if
non-LTE effects are important. Some results and astrophysical consequences are
examined.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>L. Chevallier</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">4 pages, 1 figure, conference, journal-ref updated</arxiv:comment>
