    <title>Electron Green's Function in the Planar t-J Model</title>
    <summary>  The electron Green's functions $G({\bf k},\omega)$ within the t-J model and
in the regime of intermediate doping is studied analytically using equations of
motion for projected fermionic operators and the decoupling of the self energy
into the single-particle and spin fluctuations. It is shown that the assumption
of marginal spin dynamics at T=0 leads to an anomalous quasiparticle damping.
Numerical result show also a pronounced asymmetry between the hole ($\omega&lt;0$)
and the electron ($\omega&gt;0$) part of the spectral function, whereby hole-like
quasiparticles are generally overdamped.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Peter Prelovsek</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">J. Stefan Institute, Ljubljana, Slovenia</arxiv:affiliation>
