    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9710053v1</id>
    <updated>1997-10-06T11:57:40Z</updated>
    <published>1997-10-06T11:57:40Z</published>
    <title>AC-conductance of a quantum wire with electron-electron interaction</title>
    <summary>  The complex ac-response of a quasi-one dimensional electron system in the
one-band approximation with an interaction potential of finite range is
investigated. It is shown that linear response is exact for this model. The
influence of the screening of the electric field is discussed. The complex
absorptive conductance is analyzed in terms of resistive, capacitive and
inductive behaviors.
</summary>
