  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9802021v1</id>
    <updated>1998-02-02T19:55:47Z</updated>
    <published>1998-02-02T19:55:47Z</published>
    <title>Inversion of K$_3$C$_{60}$ Reflectance Data</title>
    <summary>  We outline a procedure for obtaining the electron-phonon spectral density by
inversion of optical conductivity data, a process very similar in spirit to the
McMillan-Rowell inversion of tunelling data. We assume both electron-impurity
(elastic) and electron-phonon (inelastic) scattering processes. This procedure
has the advantage that it can be utilized in the normal state. Furthermore, a
very good qualitative result can be obtained explicitly, without iteration. We
illustrate this technique on recently acquired far-infrared data in
K$_3$C$_{60}$. We show that the electron-phonon interaction is most likely
responsible for superconductivity in these materials.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>F. Marsiglio</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Alberta/McMaster</arxiv:affiliation>
