  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9804081v1</id>
    <updated>1998-04-07T14:37:20Z</updated>
    <published>1998-04-07T14:37:20Z</published>
    <title>Forward Electron-Phonon Scattering in Normal and Superconducting States</title>
    <summary>  The sharp forward electron-phonon $(FEP)$ and impurity $(FIS)$ scattering
change the normal and superconducting properties significantly. The pseudo-gap
like features are present in the density of states for $\omega &lt;\Omega $, where
$\Omega $ is the phonon frequency. The superconducting critical temperature
$T_c$, due to the $FEP$ pairing, is linear with respect to the electron-phonon
coupling constant. The $FIS$ impurities are pair weakening for $s-$ and
$d-wave$ pairing.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>O. V. Dolgov</name>
    </author>
