  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9902241v1</id>
    <updated>1999-02-17T12:51:55Z</updated>
    <published>1999-02-17T12:51:55Z</published>
    <title>Screening, Coulomb pseudopotential, and superconductivity in
  alkali-doped Fullerenes</title>
    <summary>  We study the static screening in a Hubbard-like model using quantum Monte
Carlo. We find that the random phase approximation is surprisingly accurate
almost up to the Mott transition. We argue that in alkali-doped Fullerenes the
Coulomb pseudopotential $\mu^\ast$ is not very much reduced by retardation
effects. Therefore efficient screening is important in reducing $\mu^{\ast}$
sufficiently to allow for an electron-phonon driven superconductivity. In this
way the Fullerides differ from the conventional picture, where retardation
effects play a major role in reducing the electron-electron repulsion.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Erik Koch</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Olle Gunnarsson</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Richard M. Martin</name>
    </author>
