  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9904182v1</id>
    <updated>1999-04-13T14:26:02Z</updated>
    <published>1999-04-13T14:26:02Z</published>
    <title>Exact solution for two interacting electrons on artificial atoms and
  molecules in solids</title>
    <summary>  We present a general scheme for finding the exact eigenstates of two
electrons, with on-site repulsive potentials U_i, on I impurities in a
macroscopic crystal. The model describes impurities in doped semiconductors and
artificial molecules in quantum dots. For quantum dots, the energy cost for
adding two electrons is bounded by the single-electron spectrum, and does not
diverge when U_i approaches infinity, implying limitations on the validity of
the Coulomb blockade picture. Analytic applications on a one-dimensional chain
yield quantum delocalization and magnetic transitions.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>A. Aharony</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Tel Aviv Univ.</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
