  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9907048v1</id>
    <updated>1999-07-02T19:47:46Z</updated>
    <published>1999-07-02T19:47:46Z</published>
    <title>Screening effects in the electron-optical phonon interaction</title>
    <summary>  We show that recently reported unusual hardening of optical phonons
renormalized by the electron-phonon interaction is due to the neglect of
screening effects. When the electron-ion interaction is properly screened
optical phonons soften in three dimension. It is important that for
short-wavelength optical phonons screening is static while for long-wavelength
optical phonons screening is dynamic. In two-dimensional and one-dimensional
cases due to crossing of the nonperturbed optical mode with gapless plasmons
the spectrum of renormalized optical phonon-plasmon mode shows split momentum
dependence.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M. Reizer</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevB.61.40</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.61.40" rel="related"/>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">7 pages</arxiv:comment>
