  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/9910299v1</id>
    <updated>1999-10-20T13:28:30Z</updated>
    <published>1999-10-20T13:28:30Z</published>
    <title>Phonon spectral function for an interacting electron-phonon system</title>
    <summary>  Using exact diagonalzation techniques, we study a model of interacting
electrons and phonons. The spectral width of the phonons is found to be reduced
as the Coulomb interaction U is increased. For a system with two modes per
site, we find a transfer of coupling strength from the upper to the lower mode.
This transfer is reduced as U is increased. These results give a qualitative
explanation of differences between Raman and photoemission estimates of the
electron-phonon coupling constants for A3C60 (A= K, Rb).
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>J. E. Han</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Max-Planck-Institut fur Festkorperforschung, Stuttgart, Germany</arxiv:affiliation>
