    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0011261v1</id>
    <updated>2000-11-15T14:52:57Z</updated>
    <published>2000-11-15T14:52:57Z</published>
    <title>Theory of Strongly Correlated Electron Systems. III. Including
  Correlation Effects into Electronic Structure Calculations</title>
    <summary>  In previous papers we showed that a division of the f-shell into two
subsystems gives a better understanding of cohesive properties as well the
general behavior of lanthanide systems. In this paper we present numerical
computations using the suggested method. We show that the picture is consistent
with most experimental data, e.g. the equilibrium volume and electronic
structure in general. Compared to standard energy band calculations, or to
calculations based on the self interaction correction and LDA+U, in the present
approach f-(non-f)-mixing interaction is decreased by spectral weights of the
many-body states of the f-ion are involved.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>U. Lundin</name>
    </author>
