    <title>Wigner Crystallization in mesoscopic 2D electron systems</title>
    <summary>  Wigner crystallization of electrons in a 2D quantum dots is reported. It
proceeds in two stages: I) via radial ordering of electrons on shells and II)
freezing of the inter-shell rotation. The phase boundary of the crystal is
computed in the whole temperature--density plane, and the influence of quantum
effects and of the particle number is analyzed.
</summary>
