    <title>Electronic Mechanism of Superconductivity in the Cuprates, C$_{60}$, and
  Polyacenes</title>
    <summary>  On the basis of an analysis of theoretical and numerical studies of model
systems, and of experiments on superconductivity in doped C$_{60}$, polyacenes,
and the cuprate high temperature superconductors, we propose that a purely
electronic mechanism of superconductivity requires structures at an
intermediate or mesoscale. Specifically, we address the crucial question of how
high temperature superconducting pairing on the mesoscale can arise from purely
repulsive electronic interactions.
</summary>
