    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0208223v3</id>
    <updated>2002-11-27T21:30:06Z</updated>
    <published>2002-08-12T09:10:11Z</published>
    <title>Spin relaxation in a two-electron quantum dot</title>
    <summary>  We discuss the rate of relaxation of the total spin in the two-electron
droplet in the vicinity of the magnetic field driven singlet-triplet
transition. The total spin relaxation is attributed to spin-orbit and
electron-phonon interactions. The relaxation process is found to depend on the
spin of ground and excited states. This asymmetry is used to explain puzzles in
recent high source-drain transport experiments.
</summary>
    <author>
