  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0211665v1</id>
    <updated>2002-11-28T17:13:04Z</updated>
    <published>2002-11-28T17:13:04Z</published>
    <title>Lorenz number in high Tc superconductors: evidence for bipolarons</title>
    <summary>  Strong electron-phonon interaction in cuprates has gathered support over the
last decade in a number of experiments. While phonons remain almost
unrenormalised, electrons are transformed into itinerent bipolarons and
thermally excited polarons when the electron-phonon interaction is strong. We
calculate the Lorenz number of the system to show that the Wiedemann-Franz law
breaks down because of the interference of polaron and bipolaron contributions
in the heat flow. The model fits numerically the experimental Hall Lorenz
number, which provides a direct evidence for bipolarons in the cuprates.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>K. K. Lee</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">University of Cambridge and Loughborough University, United Kingdom</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>A. S. Alexandrov</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">University of Cambridge and Loughborough University, United Kingdom</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>W. Y. Liang</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">University of Cambridge and Loughborough University, United Kingdom</arxiv:affiliation>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.90.217001</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.90.217001" rel="related"/>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">4 page, 1 figure</arxiv:comment>
    <arxiv:journal_ref xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">Physical Review Letters, 90(21), 2003, pp 217001-1/4</arxiv:journal_ref>
