    <title>A turnstile electron-spin entangler in semiconductors</title>
    <summary>  We propose a single-electron doped quantum dot in a field-effect structure as
an optically triggered turnstile for spin-entangled electrons. A short laser
pulse excites a charged exciton, whose quantum properties are transferred
through tunneling and relaxation to the spin entanglement between electrons in
the dot and contact. We identify the pertinent disentanglement mechanisms, and
discuss experimental detection and possible application schemes.
