    <title>Effect of impurity on the determination of ground-state properties of
  parabolic quantum dot composed of N electrons</title>
    <summary>  The two dimensional Thomas-Fermi approximation is applied to the problem of
parabolic quantum dot composed of N electrons and an on-center impurity. Change
induced by impurity on electron density, chemical potential and total energy is
discussed and it is found that existence of impurity makes significant changes
on the determination of above properties especially for the small number of
electrons and strong confinements.
