  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0403742v1</id>
    <updated>2004-03-30T23:05:16Z</updated>
    <published>2004-03-30T23:05:16Z</published>
    <title>Valence-electron transfer and a metal-insulator transition in a strongly
  correlated perovskite oxide</title>
    <summary>  We present transport and thermal data for the quadruple-perovskites
MCu3(Ti1-xRux)4O12 where 0 &lt; x &lt; 1. A metal-insulator transition (MIT) occurs
for Ru concentrations x~0.75. At the same time, the Cu2+ antiferromagnetic
state is destroyed and it's magnetic entropy suppressed by Ru on a 1:1 basis.
This implies that each Ru transfers an electron to a Cu ion and thus the MIT
correlates with filling the Cu 3d shell. The Cu spin entropy in this strongly
correlated electron material provides a unique probe among MIT systems.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>A. P. Ramirez</name>
    </author>
    <author>
