  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0408229v1</id>
    <updated>2004-08-11T03:05:47Z</updated>
    <published>2004-08-11T03:05:47Z</published>
    <title>Absolute negative conductivity and zero-resistance states in two
  dimensional electron systems: A plausible scenario</title>
    <summary>  We present a model which provides a plausible explanation of the effect of
zero-resistance and zero-conductance states in two-dimensional electron systems
subjected to a magnetic field and irradiated with microwaves observed in a
number of experiments and of the effect main features. The model is based on
the concept of absolute negative conductivity associated with photon-assisted
scattering of electrons on impurities. It is shown that the main features of
the effect can be attributed to the interplay of different electron scattering
mechanisms.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>V. Ryzhii</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>A. Chaplik</name>
