    <title>Possible new bubble phases of two-dimensional electrons in higher Landau
  levels</title>
    <summary>  We argue that, due to the specific form of the interaction potential between
electronic guiding centers, a bubble crystal (BC) with basis may be
energetically more favorable than the usual bubble solid. This new BC has
well-defined normal eigenmodes, and remains energetically favorable when the
effects of finite sample thickness and of screening by electrons in lower LLs
are taken into account.
</summary>
