  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0411530v1</id>
    <updated>2004-11-20T17:44:55Z</updated>
    <published>2004-11-20T17:44:55Z</published>
    <title>Electronic excitation spectrum of metallic carbon nanotubes</title>
    <summary>  We have studied the discrete electronic spectrum of closed metallic nanotube
quantum dots. At low temperatures, the stability diagrams show a very regular
four-fold pattern that allows for the determination of the electron addition
and excitation energies. The measured nanotube spectra are in excellent
agreement with theoretical predictions based on the nanotube band structure.
Our results permit the complete identification of the electron quantum states
in nanotube quantum dots.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>S. Sapmaz</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>P. Jarillo-Herrero</name>
    </author>
