    <title>Electron-hole coupling in high-Tc cuprate superconductors</title>
    <summary>  From recent Hall effect measurements and angle-resolved photo-emission
spectroscopy the interesting picture emerges of co-existing hole- and
electron-like quasiparticle bands, both in electron- and hole-doped
superconducting cuprates. We reflect on the idea that bosonic electron-hole
pairs may be formed in the cuprates and on the possibility that these pairs
undergo Bose-Einstein condensation. The relevance to high-Tc superconductivity
in the cuprates will be discussed.
</summary>
    <author>
