  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0507319v1</id>
    <updated>2005-07-14T19:03:03Z</updated>
    <published>2005-07-14T19:03:03Z</published>
    <title>On electrons and hydrogen-bond connectivity in liquid water</title>
    <summary>  The network connectivity in liquid water is revised in terms of electronic
signatures of hydrogen bonds (HBs) instead of geometric criteria, in view of
recent X-ray absorption studies. The analysis is based on ab initio
molecular-dynamics simulations at ambient conditions. Even if instantaneous
thread-like structures are observed in the electronic network, they
continuously reshape in oscillations reminiscent of the r and t modes in ice
(tau~170 fs). However, two water molecules initially joint by a HB remain
effectively bound over many periods regardless of its electronic signature.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>M. V. Fernandez-Serra</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Emilio Artacho</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1103/PhysRevLett.96.016404</arxiv:doi>
