    <updated>2005-12-12T06:16:28Z</updated>
    <published>2005-12-12T06:16:28Z</published>
    <title>Intermediate Low Spin States in a Few-electron Quantum Dot in the
  $ν\le 1$ Regime</title>
    <summary>  We study the effects of electron-electron interactions in a circular
few-electron vertical quantum dot in such a strong magnetic field that the
filling factor $\nu\le 1$. We measure excitation spectra and find ground state
transitions beyond the maximum density droplet ($\nu=1$) region. We compare the
observed spectra with those calculated by exact diagonalization to identify the
ground state quantum numbers, and find that intermediate low-spin states occur
between adjacent spin-polarized magic number states.
</summary>
