    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0512404v1</id>
    <updated>2005-12-16T14:19:16Z</updated>
    <published>2005-12-16T14:19:16Z</published>
    <title>Line Broadening and Decoherence of Electron Spins in Phosphorus-Doped
  Silicon Due to Environmental 29^Si Nuclear Spins</title>
    <summary>  Phosphorus-doped silicon single crystals with 0.19 % &lt;= f &lt;= 99.2 %, where f
is the concentration of 29^Si isotopes, are measured at 8 K using a pulsed
electron spin resonance technique, thereby the effect of environmental 29^Si
nuclear spins on the donor electron spin is systematically studied. The
linewidth as a function of f shows a good agreement with theoretical analysis.
We also report the phase memory time T_M of the donor electron spin dependent
on both f and the crystal axis relative to the external magnetic field.
</summary>
