    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/cond-mat/0605050v1</id>
    <updated>2006-05-02T10:23:06Z</updated>
    <published>2006-05-02T10:23:06Z</published>
    <title>Single-particle spectrum for a model of fermions interacting with
  two-level local excitations on a lattice: A dynamical CPA approach</title>
    <summary>  The problem of motion of a single electron interacting with a periodic
lattice of two-level systems is investigated within a spinless fermion model.
The Green's function is calculated in a single-site dynamical coherent
potential approximation which is equivalent to DMFT. The picture of
one-electron density of states is obtained for various values of the tunnel
splitting and coupling between the electron and two-level system. The
occurrence of a band splitting with increase of the coupling is demonstrated.
</summary>
