  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ex/0508056v1</id>
    <updated>2005-08-30T08:17:46Z</updated>
    <published>2005-08-30T08:17:46Z</published>
    <title>Moments of the Electron Energy Spectrum in B --&gt; X_c l νdecays at
  Belle</title>
    <summary>  We report a measurement of the inclusive electron energy spectrum for charmed
semileptonic decays of B mesons in a 140 fb^-1 data sample collected on the
Upsilon(4S) resonance, with the Belle detector at the KEKB asymmetric energy
e^+ e^- collider. We determine the first, second and third moments of the
electron energy spectrum for threshold values of the electron energy between
0.4 and 1.5 GeV.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name> Belle Collaboration</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">13 pages, 3 figures, 6 tables, contributed to HEP2005 International
  Europhysics Conference on High Energy Physics</arxiv:comment>
    <link href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ex/0508056v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
