  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/9606303v2</id>
    <updated>1996-09-27T21:18:49Z</updated>
    <published>1996-06-11T20:48:29Z</published>
    <title>Compton Scattering on Black Body Photons</title>
    <summary>  We examine Compton scattering of electrons on black body photons in the case
where the electrons are highly relativistic, but the center of mass energy is
small in comparison with the electron mass. We derive the partial lifetime of
electrons in the LEP accelerator due to this form of scattering in the vacuum
beam pipe and compare it with previous results.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Lowell S. Brown</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>Ronald S. Steinke</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:doi xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">10.1119/1.18512</arxiv:doi>
    <link title="doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1119/1.18512" rel="related"/>
