    <title>Ultrarelativistic positronium production in collisions of high energy
  electrons and laser photons</title>
    <summary>  We consider the production of ultrarelativistic parapositronium and
orthopositronium atoms in collisions of high energy electrons with laser
photons. Our results demonstrate the opportunity of intensive positronium beam
formation with Lorentz-factor 10^6 using laser beam conversion on high energy
electrons at the future Electron Linear Accelerators.
</summary>
