  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0011340v1</id>
    <updated>2000-11-28T08:01:03Z</updated>
    <published>2000-11-28T08:01:03Z</published>
    <title>Anomalous magnetic moment of the electron in a medium</title>
    <summary>  Radiative effects are considered for an electron moving in a medium in the
presence of an external electromagnetic field. Anomalous magnetic moment (AMM)
of the electron in alpha-order is calculated under these conditions in the form
of two-dimensional integral. Behavior of AMM of high energy electron under
influence of multiple scattering in a medium is analyzed. Both mentioned
effects lead to reduction of AMM.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>V. N. Baier</name>
    </author>
    <author>
      <name>V. M. Katkov</name>
