  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0108091v2</id>
    <updated>2001-08-09T23:54:25Z</updated>
    <published>2001-08-09T22:54:23Z</published>
    <title>Recoil correction to the magnetic moment of a bound electron</title>
    <summary>  The effect of a finite nuclear mass on the magnetic moment of the electron
bound in the ground state of a hydrogen-like ion is analyzed. Using the exact
in Z\alpha expression for the recoil shift of the energy, I calculate the order
(Z\alpha)^4 m/M correction to the electron gyromagnetic ratio. The theoretical
uncertainty in the prediction for the experimentally interesting carbon ion is
decreased to the level of 1.2x10^-9. This provides a factor of two improvement
in the precision of the atomic mass of the electron.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Alexander Yelkhovsky</name>
    </author>
    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">9 pages, revtex</arxiv:comment>
    <link href="http://arxiv.org/abs/hep-ph/0108091v2" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
