    <updated>2002-06-24T16:07:15Z</updated>
    <published>2002-06-24T16:07:15Z</published>
    <title>The Phase Information Associated to Synchronized Electronic Fireflies</title>
    <summary>  An electronic implementation referring to fireflies ensembles flashing in
synchrony in a self-organization mode, shows the details of the phase-locking
mechanism and how the phases between the electronic oscillators are related to
their common period. Quantitative measurements of the timing signals link the
limits of a steadily established synchronization to the physics of the
electronic circuit. Preliminary observations suggest the existence of
bifurcation-like phenomena.
</summary>
