  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/nucl-ex/0403057v1</id>
    <updated>2004-03-30T23:24:41Z</updated>
    <published>2004-03-30T23:24:41Z</published>
    <title>The PHENIX measurement of Heavy Flavor via Single Electrons in pp, d-Au,
  and Au-Au collisions at sqrt(s_NN)=200 GeV</title>
    <summary>  The PHENIX experiment at RHIC has measured single electron spectra in
proton-proton, deuteron-gold and gold-gold collisions at sqrt(s_NN)=200 GeV.
The photonic contribution (photon conversions and Daltiz decays) is subtracted
from the inclusive spectra resulting in non-photonic electron spectra. The
principal source of non-photonic electrons is the semi-leptonic decay of charm
and bottom mesons. The implications for heavy flavor production in hot and cold
nuclear systems are discussed.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>Sean Kelly</name>
      <arxiv:affiliation xmlns:arxiv="http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom">for the PHENIX Collaboration</arxiv:affiliation>
