  <entry>
    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/physics/9807021v2</id>
    <updated>1998-08-31T10:50:42Z</updated>
    <published>1998-07-15T17:25:01Z</published>
    <title>Collimated electron jets by intense laser beam-plasma surface
  interaction under oblique incidence</title>
    <summary>  Oblique incidence of a $p$-polarized laser beam on a fully ionized plasma
with a low density plasma corona is investigated numerically by
Particle-In-Cell and Vlasov simulations in two dimensions. A single narrow
self-focused current jet of energetic electrons is observed to be projected
into the corona nearly normal to the target. Magnetic fields enhance the
penetration depth of the electrons into the corona. A scaling law for the angle
of the ejected electrons with incident laser intensity is given.
</summary>
    <author>
      <name>H. Ruhl</name>
